        {
            "message": "fix: shims break when POSIXLY_CORRECT=1\n\nProcess substitution isn't specified by POSIX and makes shims break when called by a script that `export POSIXLY_CORRECT=1` (like gitflow [here](https://github.com/nvie/gitflow/blob/develop/git-flow#L78)).\n\nHere we replace `grep -f <(cmd1) <(cmd2)` with `cmd2 | grep -F \"$(cmd1)\"` so that we can provide a string instead of a file descriptor and get the same result as before.\n\n(Note: We also check if the result of `cmd1` is empty before running `grep` to get the same behavior as with `-f`. This also prevent crashes if null results are piped to `xargs` and fits nicely with the `with_shim_executable` function that already check the result of `$selected_version` before going on).\n\nFixes: #581",
            "commit_url": "https://github.com/asdf-vm/asdf/commit/0de6910d1f99c9576f8c2e5a916644fed99cddb5",
            "removed_lines": [
                "-  grep -f <(get_shim_versions \"$shim_name\") <(preset_versions \"$shim_name\") | head -n 1 | xargs -IVERSION printf \"%s\\\\n\" VERSION"
            ],
            "added_lines": [
                "+    preset_versions \"$shim_name\" | grep -F \"$shim_versions\" | head -n 1 | xargs -IVERSION printf \"%s\\\\n\" VERSION"
            ]
        },
        {
            "message": "Make sure extension commands are properly displayed by `asdf help`",
